snippet: The competitions among Web developers for prizes for mining city government data have produced plenty of enthusiasm but less in tangible results.
abstract: App City column describes several entries in New York City's 2012 Big Apps contest, in which public agencies supply data to Web developers who compete for $50,000 in prizes; winning the contest does not necessarily lead to success in the marketplace.
lead_paragraph: The competitions among Web developers for prizes for mining city government data have produced plenty of enthusiasm but less in tangible results.

headline.print_headline: Contest Whose Winners May Not Succeed
headline.seo: New York’s BigApps Contest Has Mixed Results
headline.main: Contest Whose Winners May Not Succeed
